00:54:25,620 --> 00:54:27,770
<i>Affecting homeland security.</i>

798
00:54:27,940 --> 00:54:29,339
<i>National security...</i>

799
00:54:29,500 --> 00:54:30,695
That word is sacred.

800
00:54:39,260 --> 00:54:42,616
In Vietnam there were always
stories about Cuban advisers.

801
00:54:44,620 --> 00:54:48,500
No, it was Cubans
who were studying the Vietnamese.

802
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:51,538
To get experience.

803
00:54:51,700 --> 00:54:52,735
How many Cubans were there?

804
00:54:53,180 --> 00:54:55,171
Never more than 20, I think.

805
00:54:55,980 --> 00:54:57,379
I can't be completely sure.

806
00:54:57,860 --> 00:55:00,295
But I know it was
a very small group.

807
00:55:01,020 --> 00:55:02,579
Later it was said

808
00:55:03,260 --> 00:55:05,854
<i>that there were
security advisers there.</i>

809
00:55:07,580 --> 00:55:10,333
And that they had taken part

810
00:55:10,540 --> 00:55:12,850
in the torturing of prisoners.

811
00:55:13,020 --> 00:55:15,170
And I tell you that
that is

812
00:55:15,340 --> 00:55:16,330
absolutely untrue.

813
00:55:16,620 --> 00:55:18,452
I read the POW accounts

814
00:55:18,620 --> 00:55:20,770
in Hanoi.
We're talking about...

815
00:55:20,940 --> 00:55:25,252
I would assume two dozen men
who claim there was a Cuban

816
00:55:27,020 --> 00:55:30,092
who at first...
at first watched...

817
00:55:33,060 --> 00:55:34,494
but then participated

818
00:55:36,260 --> 00:55:38,695
in the beatings.
It was very brutal.

819
00:55:39,500 --> 00:55:40,979
If that were true,

820
00:55:41,140 --> 00:55:44,292
I assure you we would
have had them tried in a court.

821
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:48,410
Believe us or not,

822
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:53,299
I assure you that
in 43 years of Revolution

823
00:55:55,540 --> 00:55:57,338
never have we tortured anyone.

824
00:55:58,380 --> 00:56:00,530
It's a principle
of ours since the way.

825
00:56:00,700 --> 00:56:03,294
That was what Batista used to do,

826
00:56:04,100 --> 00:56:06,694
and we would never
resort to those methods.

827
00:56:06,860 --> 00:56:08,453
The Vietnamese did not want

828
00:56:08,620 --> 00:56:09,530
any foreigners

829
00:56:09,700 --> 00:56:10,815
among their troops.

830
00:56:11,500 --> 00:56:13,218
They never asked
the Chinese for help.

831
00:56:15,740 --> 00:56:18,050
They never asked the Russians.

832
00:56:18,700 --> 00:56:21,169
Oh, yes, they were very zealous...

833
00:56:22,500 --> 00:56:24,571
Deeply nationalistic.

834
00:56:25,260 --> 00:56:27,900
And the Vietnamese
were not criminals.

835
00:56:29,180 --> 00:56:34,016
The Vietnamese did not
execute their prisoners.

836
00:56:35,020 --> 00:56:36,135
There was quite
a bit of brutality.

837
00:56:36,940 --> 00:56:37,577
Well...

838
00:56:37,740 --> 00:56:39,413
He must know more than me.

839
00:56:40,580 --> 00:56:43,379
You know that we
were invaded by 1,500 men.

840
00:56:44,620 --> 00:56:46,213
We took 1,200 prisoners.

841
00:56:47,380 --> 00:56:50,338
In fighting which lasted 68 hours

842
00:56:52,100 --> 00:56:54,171
there were hundreds of wounded.

843
00:56:55,260 --> 00:56:56,489
Over 100 casualties.

844
00:56:57,940 --> 00:56:58,930
We were attacked

845
00:56:59,100 --> 00:57:00,329
by surprise,

846
00:57:01,060 --> 00:57:03,734
by planes with Cuban insignias.

847
00:57:05,420 --> 00:57:10,415
That was the source
of our... indignation.

848
00:57:11,860 --> 00:57:14,170
And rage.
A great deal of rage.

849
00:57:15,380 --> 00:57:18,816
You tell me if any
of those 1,200 prisoners...

850
00:57:18,980 --> 00:57:20,573
I myself went...

851
00:57:22,420 --> 00:57:23,330
I arrived there...

852
00:57:24,700 --> 00:57:25,576
Ask Almeida,

853
00:57:25,740 --> 00:57:26,889
ask anybody.

854
00:57:27,420 --> 00:57:29,013
Go into the streets...

855
00:57:30,540 --> 00:57:33,180
and ask if they have ever
heard about torture.

856
00:57:34,380 --> 00:57:38,374
It does not fit in
with the way we think.

857
00:57:39,780 --> 00:57:42,533
I would not have the morality
to criticize anybody.

858
00:57:42,700 --> 00:57:44,771
What about the Huberto Matos case?

859
00:57:45,180 --> 00:57:46,011
Well...

860
00:57:46,180 --> 00:57:48,296
what he did was very risky.

861
00:57:50,460 --> 00:57:52,212
He was a real coward.

862
00:57:56,980 --> 00:57:59,699
He was in the war
for the last 8 months.

863
00:58:00,660 --> 00:58:02,571
Minimal war merits...

864
00:58:03,780 --> 00:58:06,738
He wanted to get
the regiment to rebel.

865
00:58:10,500 --> 00:58:12,457
The trial

866
00:58:12,620 --> 00:58:13,530
was here.

867
00:58:14,460 --> 00:58:15,575
I went to it,

868
00:58:15,740 --> 00:58:17,538
with all the documents.

869
00:58:17,700 --> 00:58:22,058
And he was sentenced to 25 years.

870
00:58:22,460 --> 00:58:24,736
It was an act of treachery.

871
00:58:25,380 --> 00:58:26,779
A dangerous act.

872
00:59:17,900 --> 00:59:19,129
Do you think
we should walk around?

873
00:59:22,580 --> 00:59:23,695
The light's going.

874
00:59:23,860 --> 00:59:27,899
They should tell us to go
somewhere open and not too crazy.

875
00:59:32,980 --> 00:59:35,972
Wherever we go,
it will be like that.

876
00:59:38,580 --> 00:59:42,539
- It has to be a surprise.
-...the Hemingway bar?

877
00:59:43,820 --> 00:59:46,938
I'll take you,
I'll be your guide.

878
00:59:48,980 --> 00:59:51,096
Now he will be the guide.

879
00:59:51,460 --> 00:59:53,133
He will be your tourist guide.

880
01:01:47,500 --> 01:01:50,572
<i>And we say to Mr. Reagan...</i>

881
01:01:52,900 --> 01:01:57,576
<i>that we are not afraid
of his threats.</i>

882
01:01:58,260 --> 01:01:59,330
What is a dictator?

883
01:01:59,900 --> 01:02:02,096
Does anyone really know?

884
01:02:02,500 --> 01:02:05,618
Is it bad to be a dictator?

885
01:02:06,020 --> 01:02:09,297
Because I've seen the U.S.
governments, for example,

886
01:02:10,260 --> 01:02:13,616
being very friendly with
the greatest dictators.

887
01:02:14,300 --> 01:02:17,418
Marx speaks of the dictatorship
of the proletariate.

888
01:02:19,140 --> 01:02:21,939
Not of personal dictatorship.

889
01:02:27,580 --> 01:02:31,335
I have always tried
to solve basic problems

890
01:02:31,780 --> 01:02:34,693
through persuasion

891
01:02:35,780 --> 01:02:37,339
and moral authority.

892
01:02:37,500 --> 01:02:39,969
You will not find a picture

893
01:02:40,140 --> 01:02:41,130
over the last 43 years

894
01:02:42,380 --> 01:02:44,098
of police
oppressing the people.

895
01:02:50,460 --> 01:02:53,452
People all over the world call him
the "movie star dictator."

896
01:02:53,620 --> 01:02:55,099
What don't they like?

897
01:02:56,060 --> 01:02:58,051
Do they say I'm a bad actor?

898
01:02:59,540 --> 01:03:02,009
The new Evita Perén, in a way?

899
01:03:03,380 --> 01:03:04,939
Nobody denies
the real achievements.

900
01:03:06,380 --> 01:03:08,371
I have heard

901
01:03:08,540 --> 01:03:10,417
some strange things about me.

902
01:03:11,220 --> 01:03:12,540
But...

903
01:03:13,420 --> 01:03:17,653
I don't see any similarity.
I do believe that Evita Perén

904
01:03:18,340 --> 01:03:21,651
genuinely felt for
the cause of her people.

905
01:03:21,940 --> 01:03:24,614
And that the people
responded to her.

906
01:03:25,860 --> 01:03:28,170
And she had almost more support

907
01:03:29,340 --> 01:03:30,489
than Perén.

908
01:03:31,100 --> 01:03:33,979
It doesn't offend me

909
01:03:34,220 --> 01:03:36,370
if you make comparisons with her.

910
01:03:43,460 --> 01:03:46,896
I did not borrow
my ideas from anyone.

911
01:03:47,060 --> 01:03:50,337
I have always done
my job, my duty...

912
01:03:51,140 --> 01:03:54,735
I admit I am a dictator...
a dictator to myself.

913
01:03:54,900 --> 01:03:59,019
I am a dictator to myself,
a slave

914
01:03:59,180 --> 01:04:00,250
of the people.

915
01:04:01,340 --> 01:04:02,660
That's what I am.

916
01:04:06,420 --> 01:04:09,890
<i>Carlos shot a documentary
in the barrios here,</i>

917
01:04:10,060 --> 01:04:11,812
in Cuba, Havana.

918
01:04:12,660 --> 01:04:17,131
He says that in every block...
the blocks that he was shooting,

919
01:04:17,540 --> 01:04:19,258
there was always
one informant type,

920
01:04:19,420 --> 01:04:20,854
who reports...

921
01:04:23,100 --> 01:04:26,138
So people have to be cool
and they have to conform.

922
01:04:26,980 --> 01:04:28,379
It was his imagination.

923
01:04:32,540 --> 01:04:33,655
What we did today...

924
01:04:34,380 --> 01:04:36,132
What we did today,

925
01:04:36,580 --> 01:04:37,411
we could do

926
01:04:37,580 --> 01:04:39,378
in any neighborhood.

927
01:04:40,460 --> 01:04:43,532
On any street in Havana.
We can go by ourselves.

928
01:04:43,900 --> 01:04:48,098
And today you saw me
order the head of the bodyguards

929
01:04:48,940 --> 01:04:51,136
to get out of the car.

930
01:04:52,900 --> 01:04:55,779
But he's not there.
The small-time people

931
01:04:55,940 --> 01:04:58,056
drive everyone nuts, right?

932
01:04:58,220 --> 01:05:01,292
At school there's always a squealer
who makes trouble for the people.

933
01:05:02,020 --> 01:05:05,172
All states have a bureaucracy.

934
01:05:05,940 --> 01:05:08,898
And people who do different things.

935
01:05:09,060 --> 01:05:10,937
Maybe he's got to
simplify the system

936
01:05:11,100 --> 01:05:12,932
so that these guys
don't get rewarded.

937
01:05:17,700 --> 01:05:21,170
I don't like giving...

938
01:05:22,180 --> 01:05:24,057
These are different things...

939
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:27,299
It's not giving orders,
it's persuading people.

940
01:05:27,460 --> 01:05:29,895
I have been accused
of talking too much,

941
01:05:30,940 --> 01:05:33,295
but I like to persuade people.

942
01:05:33,460 --> 01:05:36,259
I don't use complicated terms.

943
01:05:36,500 --> 01:05:37,570
I converse with people.

944
01:05:56,460 --> 01:05:58,133
It's hard for me to keep still.

945
01:06:03,460 --> 01:06:06,578
What started the universe?
Was there an organizing principle?

946
01:06:11,020 --> 01:06:15,651
I think that most things
are yet to be known.

947
01:06:15,860 --> 01:06:19,091
We're only beginning to understand
the organism, cells,

948
01:06:20,260 --> 01:06:21,295
genes.

949
01:06:21,740 --> 01:06:24,175
The Pope said recently

950
01:06:24,700 --> 01:06:27,169
that the theory of evolution

951
01:06:27,540 --> 01:06:28,416
is not...

952
01:06:28,860 --> 01:06:30,737
incompatible

953
01:06:32,300 --> 01:06:35,418
with the doctrine of creation.

954
01:06:35,940 --> 01:06:37,658
The Pope also says...

955
01:06:38,100 --> 01:06:39,738
he doesn't talk about hell,

956
01:06:40,300 --> 01:06:43,292
he talks about fear of God.

957
01:06:43,580 --> 01:06:45,218
Is he an atheist?

958
01:06:46,780 --> 01:06:47,850
I do not believe.

959
01:06:48,220 --> 01:06:51,850
I do not believe in all
that man has created.

960
01:06:52,220 --> 01:06:54,973
You're an atheist but
you receive the Pope graciously.

961
01:06:56,580 --> 01:06:57,695
Do you believe

962
01:06:57,860 --> 01:06:59,737
that religion is an opiate

963
01:07:00,780 --> 01:07:01,895
for the people?

964
01:07:02,060 --> 01:07:03,812
It all depends.

965
01:07:05,380 --> 01:07:08,179
If religion is used
to create values,

966
01:07:08,340 --> 01:07:10,456
to do good, to comfort people,

967
01:07:12,420 --> 01:07:14,138
then it is not opium.

968
01:07:15,060 --> 01:07:16,858
But if religious beliefs

969
01:07:17,020 --> 01:07:20,900
are used to defend a bad cause,

970
01:07:22,220 --> 01:07:24,291
then it becomes opium.

971
01:07:25,660 --> 01:07:28,971
Religion gives consolation
to many people,

972
01:07:29,460 --> 01:07:32,020
human beings have
a tendency to believe.

973
01:07:34,660 --> 01:07:36,059
What is the meaning of your life?

974
01:07:36,860 --> 01:07:38,578
I feel satisfied with it,

975
01:07:39,940 --> 01:07:41,533
of having done what I have done.

976
01:07:43,140 --> 01:07:45,734
It gives me pleasure

977
01:07:45,900 --> 01:07:48,289
when we advance in new ideas.

978
01:07:50,340 --> 01:07:52,411
I feel absolute tranquility

979
01:07:54,420 --> 01:07:57,299
with the work done
by the Revolution.

980
01:07:58,220 --> 01:08:00,336
I would not
change it for anything.

981
01:08:03,900 --> 01:08:07,450
Does he feel that life's meaning,

982
01:08:07,620 --> 01:08:09,258
the meaning of life
for human beings,

983
01:08:09,420 --> 01:08:12,173
is to bring one closer

984
01:08:12,340 --> 01:08:14,900
to understanding oneself?

985
01:08:15,500 --> 01:08:19,209
Life is a matter
of acquiring values,

986
01:08:20,940 --> 01:08:22,613
of acquiring knowledge.

987
01:08:23,460 --> 01:08:26,498
Of doing something
worthwhile with your life.

988
01:08:27,140 --> 01:08:29,575
To practice self-control?

989
01:08:30,780 --> 01:08:31,611
Yes.

990
01:08:33,100 --> 01:08:35,296
Everything we do

991
01:08:35,460 --> 01:08:38,339
is to give real possibilities
to the people,

992
01:08:39,060 --> 01:08:41,176
to help them to develop

993
01:08:41,340 --> 01:08:43,251
their full potential.

994
01:08:44,780 --> 01:08:47,499
In the field of education,
of health...

995
01:08:48,700 --> 01:08:50,179
the cultivation of values.

996
01:08:50,660 --> 01:08:51,536
Che!

997
01:08:58,220 --> 01:09:01,338
One of the most
admirable things about Fidel

998
01:09:01,980 --> 01:09:05,496
is that of being
a historical figure, a paradigm

999
01:09:06,460 --> 01:09:09,134
who is constantly referring
to past experiences.

1000
01:09:09,660 --> 01:09:11,458
But he is still of the present.

1001
01:09:12,100 --> 01:09:14,933
And he tells us how
the future is going to be.

1002
01:09:20,260 --> 01:09:22,012
People don't live forever.

1003
01:09:22,180 --> 01:09:24,217
Man's genetic potential

1004
01:09:24,380 --> 01:09:25,734
is 120 years.

1005
01:09:26,260 --> 01:09:28,854
Turtles, 300 years.

1006
01:09:29,900 --> 01:09:31,857
Could we modify genes
and live longer?

1007
01:09:33,140 --> 01:09:34,414
It would be better.

1008
01:09:35,900 --> 01:09:37,299
Research...

1009
01:09:37,860 --> 01:09:40,329
could lead to the fountain
of youth but I think

1010
01:09:41,180 --> 01:09:43,410
that if men
could live for 500 years,

1011
01:09:45,260 --> 01:09:47,536
they would get terribly bored.

1012
01:09:50,620 --> 01:09:52,213
So he would live forever?

1013
01:09:53,140 --> 01:09:57,338
No. Because the mind
is used to the idea

1014
01:09:58,260 --> 01:10:01,093
that there is
a limited amount of time.

1015
01:10:02,020 --> 01:10:03,738
Tell him Viagra will help.

1016
01:10:06,140 --> 01:10:07,414
Help me to think?

1017
01:10:10,380 --> 01:10:16,092
As doctors say, it boosts
the circulation of the blood.

1018
01:10:17,460 --> 01:10:20,054
- I could be a CIA agent.
-That's right.

1019
01:10:20,300 --> 01:10:25,898
Then they would say, "Oliver
went to Havana to deliver Viagra."

1020
01:10:29,540 --> 01:10:33,090
They might think that it would
help to kill this enemy with

1021
01:10:33,260 --> 01:10:34,250
a heart attack.

1022
01:10:38,500 --> 01:10:41,811
He'd get the decorations
he didn't get in Vietnam.

1023
01:10:42,740 --> 01:10:44,697
Were you decorated in Vietnam?

1024
01:10:45,460 --> 01:10:46,814
Were you wounded in combat?

1025
01:10:47,060 --> 01:10:49,017
Yes, he was decorated.

1026
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:50,690
You were wounded twice?

1027
01:10:54,140 --> 01:10:56,416
That is the courage you now need

1028
01:10:57,820 --> 01:10:59,254
to do what you are doing.

1029
01:11:13,900 --> 01:11:16,050
Who's going to come after you?

1030
01:11:19,780 --> 01:11:23,136
That... all depends

1031
01:11:24,020 --> 01:11:25,977
on whether it is
in 20 years' time...

1032
01:11:28,220 --> 01:11:30,131
or 10 years' time...

1033
01:11:31,460 --> 01:11:33,337
or 6 months' time...

1034
01:11:35,020 --> 01:11:38,934
As I have always been in danger
of being assassinated,

1035
01:11:41,260 --> 01:11:45,493
since the Revolution,
I believe I have the authority

1036
01:11:46,780 --> 01:11:52,139
to go on with the Revolution.
It will not be easy.

1037
01:11:52,820 --> 01:11:54,219
I have more confidence

1038
01:11:54,380 --> 01:11:55,575
in the ideas,

1039
01:11:56,220 --> 01:11:59,178
in the political culture
of our people,

1040
01:12:00,500 --> 01:12:02,298
than in men.

1041
01:12:03,700 --> 01:12:04,815
You love her, don't you?

1042
01:12:04,980 --> 01:12:07,176
I mean she's your wife,
almost an alter-ego.

1043
01:12:11,780 --> 01:12:14,374
- Who is he talking about?
-"Her." That's me.

1044
01:12:15,060 --> 01:12:15,891
Yes.

1045
01:12:16,300 --> 01:12:19,213
She's been
my translator for years.

1046
01:12:19,380 --> 01:12:22,850
I know. your minds...
You must be husband and wife.

1047
01:12:25,100 --> 01:12:26,773
How long have you been here?

1048
01:12:26,940 --> 01:12:28,135
Almost 30 years.

1049
01:12:28,540 --> 01:12:32,374
Almost 30 years.
Very often...

1050
01:12:33,300 --> 01:12:35,610
she knows what I'm thinking

1051
01:12:36,340 --> 01:12:38,251
and she goes ahead of me.

1052
01:12:38,860 --> 01:12:40,294
What about in his heart?

1053
01:12:40,460 --> 01:12:41,655
Does he love you?

1054
01:12:45,540 --> 01:12:46,450
Yes.

1055
01:12:46,620 --> 01:12:47,940
In my heart, yes.

1056
01:12:48,300 --> 01:12:49,893
What is he getting at?

1057
01:12:50,580 --> 01:12:54,050
I want him
to acknowledge his heart.

1058
01:12:59,580 --> 01:13:01,617
Yes, he wants to know everything.

1059
01:13:03,020 --> 01:13:07,139
It is hard to get away
from his questioning.

1060
01:13:07,820 --> 01:13:11,211
- You love him though.
-Yes, of course, I love him too.

1061
01:13:13,260 --> 01:13:16,491
I asked earlier if
you had a picture of Dalia.

1062
01:13:22,420 --> 01:13:23,899
I have some pictures.

1063
01:13:24,100 --> 01:13:28,014
But it does not seem
proper to show them.

1064
01:13:28,180 --> 01:13:30,490
That is what
I have always believed.

1065
01:13:33,060 --> 01:13:35,973
The other girls are visible. Is it
that her pictures are hard to find?

1066
01:13:36,140 --> 01:13:37,574
Which other girls?

1067
01:13:39,300 --> 01:13:41,496
Nati... the first wife...

1068
01:13:42,100 --> 01:13:43,090
Mirta.

1069
01:13:44,500 --> 01:13:45,649
Cecilia.

1070
01:13:52,700 --> 01:13:54,099
There are some names

1071
01:13:55,380 --> 01:13:56,734
I do not recognize.

1072
01:13:57,540 --> 01:13:59,019
There must be a mistake.

1073
01:14:00,580 --> 01:14:01,934
No, one was Nati.

1074
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:05,099
Nati, I know her.

1075
01:14:05,420 --> 01:14:07,058
Celia Sénchez?

1076
01:14:08,020 --> 01:14:10,170
I know Celia Sénchez.

1077
01:14:10,740 --> 01:14:12,174
And the first wife.

1078
01:14:13,420 --> 01:14:16,538
Yes, but you said before
"Cecilia" instead of Celia.

1079
01:14:16,700 --> 01:14:19,658
- It's a different name in Spanish.
-Let me say...

1080
01:14:20,620 --> 01:14:22,657
it has always been
a habit with me

1081
01:14:23,380 --> 01:14:26,736
that I don't think I have a right
to talk about relationships

1082
01:14:26,900 --> 01:14:29,130
I have had with ladies.

1083
01:14:32,220 --> 01:14:33,733
That is my first rule.

1084
01:14:35,540 --> 01:14:37,929
Not even with
the mother of his sons?

1085
01:14:43,180 --> 01:14:46,172
She may be the mother
of my sons and she may not be.

1086
01:14:50,060 --> 01:14:51,698
Well, she's married officially, no?

1087
01:14:52,100 --> 01:14:52,817
No.

1088
01:14:56,300 --> 01:14:58,018
A formality I have avoided.

1089
01:14:59,780 --> 01:15:01,259
I married once.

1090
01:15:02,060 --> 01:15:03,619
I did not need to again.

1091
01:15:04,820 --> 01:15:06,458
So...

1092
01:15:06,740 --> 01:15:08,219
really...

1093
01:15:10,180 --> 01:15:15,129
when you asked me about Mirta...

1094
01:15:16,500 --> 01:15:19,333
She knew she was marrying
a revolutionary.

1095
01:15:22,300 --> 01:15:24,940
Why do people say
Celia was the great love?

1096
01:15:25,820 --> 01:15:29,017
She was an extraordinary woman.

1097
01:15:30,500 --> 01:15:33,458
It was a different
kind of relationship.

1098
01:15:34,860 --> 01:15:38,012
And I've never talked about that.

1099
01:15:48,100 --> 01:15:50,376
It has not been
a life without love.

1100
01:15:51,940 --> 01:15:53,453
It has has been a life...

1101
01:15:55,140 --> 01:15:56,255
with love.

1102
01:15:57,460 --> 01:16:00,020
It is a story I do not
have the right to make public.

1103
01:16:08,260 --> 01:16:09,295
He reminds me of my father.

1104
01:16:09,460 --> 01:16:11,531
For that generation,
it's a little bit

1105
01:16:11,700 --> 01:16:13,976
harder to talk about
private affairs.

1106
01:16:16,900 --> 01:16:17,935
<i>Fidelito.</i>

1107
01:16:21,740 --> 01:16:23,651
<i>- Hello, Fidel Junior.
-Hi.</i>

1108
01:16:24,140 --> 01:16:27,132
<i>That': a very good-looking puppy
you have there. ls he yours?</i>

1109
01:16:27,300 --> 01:16:28,893
<i>No, somebody</i>

1110
01:16:29,060 --> 01:16:31,017
<i>gave it to my father.</i>

1111
01:16:31,500 --> 01:16:34,299
Has he been a good father?
I mean he's been so busy.

1112
01:16:38,500 --> 01:16:40,776
Politically, as a revolutionary,

1113
01:16:41,620 --> 01:16:44,851
I refuse to mix
my family with politics.

1114
01:16:45,780 --> 01:16:48,454
Really, the idea of First Ladies...

1115
01:16:49,380 --> 01:16:51,530
seems ridiculous to me.

1116
01:16:51,700 --> 01:16:53,930
The time I have devoted
to my children

1117
01:16:55,500 --> 01:16:56,979
has not been so much.

1118
01:16:57,780 --> 01:17:00,932
If you measure
my being a good father

1119
01:17:02,500 --> 01:17:04,377
by time spent with them,

1120
01:17:04,540 --> 01:17:08,659
then perhaps
I have not been a good father.

1121
01:17:09,300 --> 01:17:12,179
But I am capable of feeling...

1122
01:17:13,580 --> 01:17:16,333
and I do feel for them

1123
01:17:16,500 --> 01:17:19,379
even though I do not spend
all day with them.

1124
01:17:22,180 --> 01:17:24,057
When I am with them

1125
01:17:25,260 --> 01:17:28,252
I try to make the most of
the time we have together.

1126
01:17:45,660 --> 01:17:50,177
Why, if Mr. Castro...
I feel he's very popular

1127
01:17:50,340 --> 01:17:52,092
with young people, a new generation
70 or 80 percent...?

1128
01:17:54,660 --> 01:17:56,219
Why not have an election now?

1129
01:17:58,940 --> 01:18:01,739
That is the wrong

1130
01:18:02,700 --> 01:18:03,656
question.

1131
01:18:04,580 --> 01:18:06,378
Because it is based

1132
01:18:06,540 --> 01:18:07,575
on the assumption

1133
01:18:08,540 --> 01:18:10,736
that there is no
electoral system in Cuba,

1134
01:18:11,780 --> 01:18:14,056
and that there
are no elections here.

1135
01:18:15,340 --> 01:18:16,330
Possibly

1136
01:18:16,500 --> 01:18:20,698
our elections are much more
democratic than in other countries.

1137
01:18:20,860 --> 01:18:22,259
He should study

1138
01:18:24,620 --> 01:18:27,214
our electoral system,

1139
01:18:28,140 --> 01:18:30,893
the participation
of all our citizens,

1140
01:18:31,340 --> 01:18:33,616
who elect delegates
from every region.

1141
01:18:34,580 --> 01:18:35,490
The Party

1142
01:18:35,940 --> 01:18:38,056
does not put up candidates.

1143
01:18:38,860 --> 01:18:42,012
It is the citizens who choose.

1144
01:18:42,180 --> 01:18:44,820
You cannot start
from the assumption

1145
01:18:44,980 --> 01:18:46,459
that there are no elections.

1146
01:18:49,500 --> 01:18:50,979
What about the government's

1147
01:18:51,140 --> 01:18:53,370
discrimination
against homosexuals?

1148
01:18:54,420 --> 01:18:58,254
At the beginning
in this country there was

1149
01:19:00,060 --> 01:19:02,734
a machista spirit...

1150
01:19:03,980 --> 01:19:05,334
<i>machista...</i>

1151
01:19:10,340 --> 01:19:14,538
and prejudice.
Over the years

1152
01:19:14,700 --> 01:19:16,737
that has declined

1153
01:19:17,620 --> 01:19:19,770
to the point where
there is practically

1154
01:19:22,460 --> 01:19:25,737
no kind of problem.

1155
01:19:26,300 --> 01:19:32,057
It has been difficult due to
our male-dominated heritage.

1156
01:19:32,340 --> 01:19:34,251
What about the black population?

1157
01:19:34,420 --> 01:19:35,376
Well...

1158
01:19:36,180 --> 01:19:39,298
the black population
is the poorest.

1159
01:19:42,980 --> 01:19:44,334
But it also benefited most

1160
01:19:44,500 --> 01:19:45,854
from the Revolution.

1161
01:19:46,020 --> 01:19:47,135
Thanks to him,

1162
01:19:47,300 --> 01:19:48,256
I have what I have.

1163
01:19:48,420 --> 01:19:50,934
"I have what I should have,"
as Nicolas Guillén said.

1164
01:19:52,300 --> 01:19:53,529
Thanks to him.

1165
01:19:54,940 --> 01:19:56,738
Believe me, from my heart...

1166
01:19:57,380 --> 01:19:59,610
They are the most revolutionary.

1167
01:20:01,860 --> 01:20:04,295
Are there any black
political leaders?

1168
01:20:07,340 --> 01:20:09,809
Yes, we have black
political leaders,

1169
01:20:09,980 --> 01:20:12,210
but we are still not satisfied.

1170
01:20:12,780 --> 01:20:15,215
I think that we have still not

1171
01:20:15,380 --> 01:20:20,409
achieved the true possibility
of equal opportunities.

1172
01:20:23,900 --> 01:20:25,811
What's going to happen
in Colombia right now?

1173
01:20:26,940 --> 01:20:27,975
There came a point

1174
01:20:28,500 --> 01:20:30,855
where the ceasefire was broken...

1175
01:20:32,380 --> 01:20:36,169
and negotiations
were broken off.

1176
01:20:38,100 --> 01:20:41,536
And this may lead to

1177
01:20:41,700 --> 01:20:42,895
a very bloody war.

1178
01:20:44,740 --> 01:20:46,777
So he sees another Vietnam?

1179
01:20:46,940 --> 01:20:49,090
What I see is a civil war.

1180
01:20:50,140 --> 01:20:52,336
I could not
compare it to Vietnam

1181
01:20:53,740 --> 01:20:57,574
because events do not take place
in exactly the same way.

1182
01:20:59,220 --> 01:21:01,336
Without any doubt it will be

1183
01:21:02,700 --> 01:21:05,340
complicated as there
are different forces.

1184
01:21:12,740 --> 01:21:15,698
If there is a power structure
that runs the world,

1185
01:21:17,780 --> 01:21:19,930
would you want Nelson Mandela

1186
01:21:20,100 --> 01:21:21,738
to have a neutron bomb?

1187
01:21:28,620 --> 01:21:32,375
No. I know something about that...

1188
01:21:33,460 --> 01:21:35,576
My deepest conviction

1189
01:21:37,500 --> 01:21:38,570
is that

1190
01:21:39,220 --> 01:21:42,611
he does not even know
where those weapons are.

1191
01:21:44,060 --> 01:21:45,937
I spoke with Mandela about that.

1192
01:21:46,100 --> 01:21:49,980
I asked him what he knew
about those nuclear weapons.

1193
01:21:51,060 --> 01:21:53,336
And what the military had told him.

1194
01:21:53,540 --> 01:21:56,419
Where were they? And he said,

1195
01:21:57,340 --> 01:21:58,853
that he'd been told

1196
01:22:00,300 --> 01:22:03,372
that they had been destroyed,

1197
01:22:04,300 --> 01:22:06,576
that they had been disarmed.

1198
01:22:09,660 --> 01:22:11,697
There's a movie in America now

1199
01:22:11,860 --> 01:22:16,696
showing America as powerful,
America patriotic, nationalistic...

1200
01:22:19,580 --> 01:22:22,094
fighting wars against

1201
01:22:22,380 --> 01:22:23,290
terrorism...

1202
01:22:23,460 --> 01:22:24,609
drugs...

1203
01:22:27,420 --> 01:22:31,937
The army is very scary,
the weapons are very scary.

1204
01:22:32,100 --> 01:22:33,056
Where is this going?

1205
01:22:36,700 --> 01:22:39,533
That's the same question
many of us ask.

1206
01:22:41,460 --> 01:22:43,451
I think that the world

1207
01:22:44,300 --> 01:22:47,099
will become more
and more ungovernable.

1208
01:22:50,260 --> 01:22:52,137
It is impossible

1209
01:22:52,500 --> 01:22:55,618
to establish a world order

1210
01:22:56,740 --> 01:22:58,492
based on force.

1211
01:23:00,180 --> 01:23:03,457
The solution to the world's
problems is not a military one.

1212
01:23:05,380 --> 01:23:09,419
I have the hope
that the American people

1213
01:23:10,060 --> 01:23:12,449
will play a decisive role

1214
01:23:13,940 --> 01:23:17,092
in defending changes

1215
01:23:18,300 --> 01:23:19,699
for a more humane order.

1216
01:23:20,860 --> 01:23:23,852
Che said many Vietnams
will bring down America.

1217
01:23:24,660 --> 01:23:27,812
From a strategic point
of view, his way of thinking

1218
01:23:27,980 --> 01:23:31,177
was right.
Not "bring down America."

1219
01:23:31,540 --> 01:23:35,613
I never heard Che say
"bring down America."

1220
01:23:35,780 --> 01:23:37,896
The U.S. is the U.S. people.

1221
01:23:38,380 --> 01:23:41,099
First of all put
an end to corruption,

1222
01:23:41,700 --> 01:23:43,259
and put an end

1223
01:23:43,420 --> 01:23:44,535
to abuses,

1224
01:23:45,220 --> 01:23:48,178
to repression in this hemisphere.

1225
01:23:48,540 --> 01:23:50,531
That was Che's first priority.

1226
01:23:51,340 --> 01:23:53,138
He meant the fight

1227
01:23:53,300 --> 01:23:55,018
against colonialism...

1228
01:23:55,180 --> 01:23:58,298
That is what Che meant by that.

1229
01:24:00,740 --> 01:24:02,458
People who I have talked to before

1230
01:24:03,660 --> 01:24:05,936
told me that Che, he came back

1231
01:24:06,100 --> 01:24:07,215
from Africa,

1232
01:24:08,060 --> 01:24:10,700
they told me he had
two nervous breakdowns,

1233
01:24:12,420 --> 01:24:14,730
and he came back here,
went to a clinic,

1234
01:24:15,700 --> 01:24:16,770
he had a 48-hour

1235
01:24:16,940 --> 01:24:19,090
meeting with Fidel and then he...

1236
01:24:19,820 --> 01:24:21,857
he slammed the door
on the way out

1237
01:24:23,780 --> 01:24:25,134
and then he went to Bolivia.

1238
01:24:33,060 --> 01:24:34,892
If history is written like that,

1239
01:24:36,340 --> 01:24:38,377
then I would never read it again.

1240
01:24:41,900 --> 01:24:44,574
<i>Here is a letter</i>

1241
01:24:44,740 --> 01:24:47,892
<i>from our comrade
Ernesto Guevara...</i>

1242
01:24:49,060 --> 01:24:49,891
<i>“Fidel,</i>

1243
01:24:51,580 --> 01:24:53,651
<i>I feel I have fulfilled that part</i>

1244
01:24:53,820 --> 01:24:55,697
<i>of my duty</i>

1245
01:24:55,860 --> 01:24:58,090
<i>that bound me
to the Cuban Revolution</i>

1246
01:24:58,260 --> 01:25:02,299
<i>on its territory
and now [leave you,</i>

1247
01:25:02,460 --> 01:25:04,019
<i>the comrades,</i>

1248
01:25:04,180 --> 01:25:06,569
<i>and your people,
which is also mine.“</i>

1249
01:25:07,700 --> 01:25:08,770
The truth is...

1250
01:25:09,700 --> 01:25:11,976
that when he joined us in Mexico

1251
01:25:13,460 --> 01:25:14,655
he asked for one thing.

1252
01:25:14,820 --> 01:25:17,130
That when the Cuban Revolution
was complete,

1253
01:25:18,700 --> 01:25:20,737
he wanted to go on.

1254
01:25:21,820 --> 01:25:24,050
And he did not want,

1255
01:25:24,220 --> 01:25:25,654
for reasons of state,

1256
01:25:28,100 --> 01:25:30,933
us to forbid him to go.

1257
01:25:31,100 --> 01:25:33,250
That was the idea he had in mind.

1258
01:25:35,620 --> 01:25:36,496
I heard that

1259
01:25:36,660 --> 01:25:37,695
he pissed off people.

1260
01:25:38,260 --> 01:25:40,410
That he was not a compromiser.

1261
01:25:40,700 --> 01:25:44,216
And I heard that
he embarrassed Cuba

1262
01:25:44,380 --> 01:25:47,577
because he attacked the Russians and
the Russians were upset with him.

1263
01:25:47,740 --> 01:25:49,139
He was critical

1264
01:25:50,420 --> 01:25:53,492
of the use
of capitalist categories

1265
01:25:55,660 --> 01:25:58,459
to build socialism.

1266
01:25:59,380 --> 01:26:02,054
Did the Soviets tell Fidel
to get rid of him, put him away?

1267
01:26:02,820 --> 01:26:05,334
Never. That would be
like asking me

1268
01:26:06,220 --> 01:26:09,417
to get rid of Raul.

1269
01:26:09,580 --> 01:26:11,890
A man would say the motivation
might very well be that he was...

1270
01:26:12,060 --> 01:26:14,210
Che goes to Africa,

1271
01:26:14,620 --> 01:26:18,579
where he has a mostly successful
experience, comes back

1272
01:26:18,740 --> 01:26:20,731
and Cuba must seem
very small to him.

1273
01:26:20,900 --> 01:26:23,414
He wants to expand right away.

1274
01:26:24,540 --> 01:26:26,178
I sent him to Africa,

1275
01:26:27,500 --> 01:26:28,899
and I'll tell you why.

1276
01:26:29,420 --> 01:26:31,491
He was very impatient.

1277
01:26:33,180 --> 01:26:34,215
He wanted to go

1278
01:26:34,380 --> 01:26:35,495
to South America.

1279
01:26:35,740 --> 01:26:38,573
I did not believe
that conditions were still right

1280
01:26:40,300 --> 01:26:43,531
and that we still had to fulfill
our mission in Africa.

1281
01:26:43,980 --> 01:26:45,095
Because

1282
01:26:46,780 --> 01:26:48,214
he was very impatient

1283
01:26:49,140 --> 01:26:51,177
and guerrillas need to be young.

1284
01:26:52,900 --> 01:26:53,935
Some people said

1285
01:26:54,220 --> 01:26:55,654
that Fidel could have

1286
01:26:55,820 --> 01:26:58,380
put more pressure in Bolivia

1287
01:26:58,540 --> 01:26:59,610
to help Che.

1288
01:27:00,540 --> 01:27:02,770
That was a combined operation.

1289
01:27:04,020 --> 01:27:05,579
It would have taken time.

1290
01:27:07,260 --> 01:27:10,059
It was a guerrilla struggle
in its first phase.

1291
01:27:11,820 --> 01:27:13,299
When you initiate it,

1292
01:27:14,020 --> 01:27:17,092
the terrain, the people
are unfamiliar.

1293
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:22,892
And I wanted him to get
there with the utmost safety.

1294
01:27:23,820 --> 01:27:26,255
But differences arose between him...

1295
01:27:30,060 --> 01:27:31,858
rivalry on the part of

1296
01:27:34,420 --> 01:27:36,855
the leader of the
Communist Party leader.

1297
01:27:37,060 --> 01:27:39,779
There were contradictions.

1298
01:27:41,900 --> 01:27:43,413
<i>Other lands</i>

1299
01:27:43,580 --> 01:27:48,654
<i>call for my modest efforts.</i>

1300
01:27:49,500 --> 01:27:52,299
<i>To my children, to my wife,
I do not leave</i>

1301
01:27:52,980 --> 01:27:56,291
<i>anything material,
and I do not regret it.</i>

1302
01:27:57,460 --> 01:27:59,178
<i>I am happy that it is so.</i>

1303
01:27:59,980 --> 01:28:03,177
<i>I do not ask for anything
for them because the state</i>

1304
01:28:03,340 --> 01:28:05,616
<i>will provide all they need to live</i>

1305
01:28:05,780 --> 01:28:06,975
<i>and to be educated.</i>

1306
01:28:17,580 --> 01:28:18,809
I'm going to quote

1307
01:28:18,980 --> 01:28:21,176
an actor, Vittorio Gassman.
He was interviewed

1308
01:28:21,340 --> 01:28:23,331
when he was 70.
He said,

1309
01:28:23,500 --> 01:28:25,377
"Life should be lived twice.

1310
01:28:25,540 --> 01:28:29,898
The first time is a rehearsal, and
the second time we'd live for real."

1311
01:28:32,540 --> 01:28:34,292
Always back to philosophy.

1312
01:28:39,380 --> 01:28:40,336
I wish...

1313
01:28:41,660 --> 01:28:43,697
we could think of life

1314
01:28:44,740 --> 01:28:46,378
as in two parts.

1315
01:28:46,660 --> 01:28:48,458
One part as a rehearsal

1316
01:28:50,100 --> 01:28:51,056
and the other part

1317
01:28:52,060 --> 01:28:53,175
as the real thing.

1318
01:28:54,860 --> 01:28:58,216
It happened to him,
to me, to everyone.

1319
01:29:00,940 --> 01:29:02,817
Yes, but there are things
in all our lives...

1320
01:29:02,980 --> 01:29:05,494
So possibly twice...

1321
01:29:07,340 --> 01:29:09,616
It's enough to be born just once.

1322
01:29:10,860 --> 01:29:11,895
Did he make mistakes?

1323
01:29:14,420 --> 01:29:16,138
Yes, like everyone.

1324
01:29:19,220 --> 01:29:22,417
Life is a process
of learning ideas, values.

1325
01:29:24,940 --> 01:29:27,090
We are not born with ideas.

1326
01:29:28,060 --> 01:29:31,496
We are not born with values.

1327
01:29:32,500 --> 01:29:34,537
We are taught those things.

1328
01:29:36,020 --> 01:29:39,536
Or to a certain extent
we teach them to ourselves.

1329
01:29:44,900 --> 01:29:46,652
Is there any
specific moment, regret,

1330
01:29:46,820 --> 01:29:48,254
political, personal,

1331
01:29:48,420 --> 01:29:50,855
that you would just
go back now and change it?

1332
01:29:56,100 --> 01:29:57,499
If I were born again...

1333
01:29:58,300 --> 01:30:00,576
I would be the same as I am now...

1334
01:30:04,300 --> 01:30:08,851
given that I was born
under the same circumstances.

1335
01:30:16,740 --> 01:30:18,970
<i>Let us not fool ourselves
into thinking</i>

1336
01:30:20,980 --> 01:30:23,335
<i>that what lies ahead will be easy.</i>

1337
01:30:26,380 --> 01:30:28,974
<i>Perhaps what lies ahead</i>

1338
01:30:30,060 --> 01:30:31,130
<i>will all be</i>

1339
01:30:31,300 --> 01:30:32,290
<i>more difficult.</i>

1340
01:31:43,100 --> 01:31:44,329
I have

1341
01:31:44,500 --> 01:31:47,652
to take you to the airport.
That's my only guarantee.

1342
01:31:48,220 --> 01:31:49,051
Let's go.

1343
01:31:55,580 --> 01:31:57,617
Oliver, don't waste
another minute.

1344
01:31:59,500 --> 01:32:01,252
It's a Mexican plane.

1345
01:32:20,100 --> 01:32:23,013
No flowers or gifts,
we'll mail them to you.

1346
01:32:26,780 --> 01:32:28,771
Life is good to you.

1347
01:32:31,460 --> 01:32:33,212
Same here.

1348
01:32:34,980 --> 01:32:38,257
It was good because
it brought you here.

1349
01:32:41,060 --> 01:32:42,380
Many, many thanks.

1350
01:32:42,540 --> 01:32:43,291
Thank you.

1351
01:32:47,060 --> 01:32:48,459
Good luck.

1352
01:32:59,780 --> 01:33:02,499
Leave him here
so we can feed him up.

1353
01:33:03,060 --> 01:33:05,700
That would be good,
to do some volunteer work.

1354
01:33:30,260 --> 01:33:34,652
<i>Those who would give up essential Liberty
to obtain a little temporary Safety</i>

1355
01:33:34,860 --> 01:33:37,932
<i>deserve neither Liberty
nor Safety. Benjamin Franklin.</i>

